.TH KANBANANA 1 "March 2026" "kanbanana 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kanbanana \- local orchestration board for coding agents
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kanbanana
.RI [ --port " " number ]
.RI [ --agent " " id ]
.RI [ --no-open ]
.RI [ --help ]
.RI [ --version ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kanbanana
starts the local Kanbanana runtime server and serves the web UI.

When launched inside a git repository, it opens that repository's indexed workspace.
When launched outside git, it starts with no active workspace or falls back to the first indexed project.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --port <number>
Bind to a specific local port (default: 8484).
.TP
.B --agent <id>
Set the default agent command to one of: claude, codex, gemini, opencode, cline.
.TP
.B --no-open
Do not open the browser automatically.
.TP
.B --help, -h
Show help text and exit.
.TP
.B --version, -v
Show version and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start server on the default port:
.B kanbanana
.TP
Start server without auto-opening a browser:
.B kanbanana --no-open
.TP
Start server on a custom port:
.B kanbanana --port 9000
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful execution.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR npm (1)
